# Project Context — gald3r

> Goose reads `.goosehints` (project root) as project-specific instructions that
> customize Goose behavior. Edit the canonical copy under
> `.gald3r_sys/platforms/.goose/` — not the installed copy.
>
> NOTE: `.goosehints` is the correct Goose instruction file — NOT `GOOSE.md`
> (which is not a Goose convention). See PLATFORM_SPEC.md in this folder.

## Task Management
All tasks are tracked in `.gald3r/TASKS.md`. Before implementing, read the active task in
`.gald3r/tasks/task{id}_*.md`. Read `.gald3r/CONSTRAINTS.md` before architectural changes.

## Commit Convention
- `feat(T{id}): description` — new task work
- `fix(BUG-{id}): description` — bug fix

## Bug Protocol
Pre-existing bugs: document in `.gald3r/BUGS.md` — never silently ignore.

## gald3r MCP (optional)
In Goose, extensions ARE MCP servers. Add the gald3r MCP server as an extension in the
GLOBAL config at `~/.config/goose/config.yaml` (machine-specific) — there is no project
`.goose/config.yaml` convention. See `goose_instructions.md` for the example snippet.
